The paper deals with document structure analysis, which is a problem in computer vision and machine learning. The proposed architecture is based on graph networks, which are commonly used in the field of artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the lack of large scale datasets, which is a common issue in natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, since the paper deals with text and document processing, it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
